Fuse with KOH in presence of air or oxidising agents like $\mathrm{KNO}_3$ , $\mathrm{KClO}_3$ etc.
$\begin{aligned}
& 2 \mathrm{MnO}_2+4 \mathrm{KOH}+\mathrm{O}_2 \xrightarrow{\text { fuse }} 2 \mathrm{~K}_2 \mathrm{MnO}_4+2 \mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{O} \\
& \mathrm{MnO}_4{ }^{2-} \xrightarrow{\text { electrolytic oxidation }} \mathrm{MnO}_4^{-}+\mathrm{e}^{-}
\end{aligned}$
